Job Description
An exciting opportunity has arisen for Quality Lead working for one of the world leading operators. The role will start in London moving out to the Middle East based for contractor offices, overlooking quality management and integrity to ensure the fabrication level is up to company standard. Key aspects of the position include: • The development and implementation of project quality assurance and quality control activities identified within the Project Quality Plan.• Application of the requirements of the COMPANY’s Engineering and Quality Management Guidelines and associated quality related guidance documents.• Providing guidance, advice and training to project team, contractors, suppliers, inspectors and third parties (as required) to ensure understanding of the project’s Quality objectives. Previous experience within this niche is essential and previous experience in heading contractor engineering in the middle east for fabrication of an onshore gas facility extension will be highly advantageous. An attractive day rate awaits the successful applicant along with scope for ongoing progression.
